01:15.834 --> 01:19.067
<i>And for $100, name the chief
export of the United States.</i>

01:19.102 --> 01:20.501
Wheat.

01:20.536 --> 01:21.701
<i>Machinery.</i>

01:21.736 --> 01:23.067
<i>Machinery is correct.</i>

01:23.102 --> 01:25.234
<i>Now, which state produced
the most U.S. presidents?</i>

01:25.269 --> 01:26.234
Illinois.

01:26.269 --> 01:27.234
<i>Virginia.</i>

01:27.269 --> 01:28.501
<i>Virginia is correct.</i>

01:28.536 --> 01:30.334
<i>Which side of the brain</i>

01:30.369 --> 01:31.901
<i>controls
analytical thinking?</i>

01:31.936 --> 01:32.901
The right.

01:32.936 --> 01:33.901
<i>The left.</i>

01:33.936 --> 01:35.400
<i>The left is correct!</i>

01:35.435 --> 01:38.701
<i>And we'll be right back after
this brief commercial message.</i>

01:38.736 --> 01:40.033
<i>Hey, America.</i>

01:40.068 --> 01:42.067
<i>Who do you call when
you don't want to cook?</i>

01:42.102 --> 01:43.334
Ahab's.

01:43.369 --> 01:45.167
<i>Ahab's is correct.</i>

01:45.202 --> 01:47.601
<i>Yes. Ahab's
for fish and fowl.</i>

01:47.636 --> 01:48.934
<i>Yes, opening soon</i>

01:48.969 --> 01:51.033
<i>in an economically
depressed area near you.</i>

01:52.502 --> 01:53.534
Daddy's home. Come on.

01:59.100 --> 02:01.901
Hi, honey. How was your day
at the shoe store?

02:01.936 --> 02:03.267
I'll tell you
something, Peg.

02:03.302 --> 02:05.968
Feet and the return
of warm weather

02:06.003 --> 02:08.434
sure makes for
a deadly combination.

02:09.834 --> 02:12.534
Well, you knew that
going in, Al.

02:12.569 --> 02:15.133
Yeah. My back is so tight.

02:16.400 --> 02:19.467
I wish I had
somebody to rub it.

02:19.502 --> 02:20.968
Like a wife.

02:22.834 --> 02:24.801
Hey, there's one now!

02:26.901 --> 02:28.400
How about my back?

02:28.435 --> 02:30.968
You know, Al, I work hard
all day too.

02:31.003 --> 02:32.300
Yeah? Doing what?

02:36.901 --> 02:37.801
Ahh!

02:39.300 --> 02:42.100
Ohh, that feels good.

02:42.135 --> 02:43.434
How good?

02:50.868 --> 02:52.367
Where are the kids?

02:52.402 --> 02:53.467
Upstairs.

02:53.502 --> 02:55.334
What if they come down?

02:55.369 --> 02:56.767
I'll take care of that.

02:56.802 --> 02:58.000
Bud, Kelly!

02:58.035 --> 03:00.868
You want to come down
and help me in the kitchen?

03:04.067 --> 03:06.868
There. That should
buy us about 10 minutes.

03:06.903 --> 03:09.434
Seven more
than we'll need.

03:13.534 --> 03:14.934
Where were we?

03:17.934 --> 03:19.000
We're here, Bundy!

03:21.734 --> 03:23.734
Bundy, Bundy,
don't you know

03:23.769 --> 03:26.467
you shouldn't leave
your door unlocked?

03:26.502 --> 03:29.868
It's an invitation
to intruders.

03:29.903 --> 03:31.901
What are they
doing here?

03:31.936 --> 03:34.968
They're the neighborhood watch.
I invited them.

03:35.003 --> 03:36.434
To watch this?!

03:37.667 --> 03:40.367
Uh, hi, Peggy. Al.

03:40.402 --> 03:42.634
I hope we're not
interrupting anything.

03:42.669 --> 03:45.734
Nah. Just gonna have
a little sex with the wife.

03:48.868 --> 03:51.267
What the heck.
There's always next month.

03:52.501 --> 03:54.734
Our house was robbed
this afternoon.

03:54.769 --> 03:58.033
Gee, that's too bad.
You wanna hand me my shirt?

03:58.068 --> 04:00.267
What did
they steal?

04:00.302 --> 04:02.000
Mostly small stuff.

04:02.035 --> 04:03.501
Our radio,
Marcie's earrings,

04:03.536 --> 04:05.501
our cameras,
our answering machine.

04:05.536 --> 04:07.868
God only knows
who called.

04:09.434 --> 04:12.334
Well, at least they didn't
take anything valuable.

04:12.369 --> 04:13.734
Yeah, this time.

04:13.769 --> 04:15.400
But I know how
these vermin think.

04:15.435 --> 04:16.733
They take your little crap,

04:16.769 --> 04:19.934
then come back later with
a truck for your big crap.

04:19.969 --> 04:21.934
Not gonna happen
in my house.

04:21.969 --> 04:23.234
I'm ready for them.

04:23.269 --> 04:25.868
I got 50,000 volts going
through my window bars.

04:25.903 --> 04:29.467
I got a bucket of battery acid
hanging over the back door

04:29.502 --> 04:32.334
and I got a.30-aught-6
rigged to the front doorknob.

04:32.369 --> 04:34.300
How do you get into
your house?

04:34.335 --> 04:36.133
Wouldn't you
like to know?

04:37.934 --> 04:40.067
Now, the question
before us is:

04:40.102 --> 04:42.801
What are we gonna
do about it?

04:42.836 --> 04:45.200
I say we hunt
the scum down,

04:45.235 --> 04:47.567
and then we run them over
with our cars.

04:47.602 --> 04:49.434
Then we get out
these fishhooks-

04:49.469 --> 04:50.434
Marcie!

04:50.469 --> 04:51.501
I'm sorry.

04:51.536 --> 04:54.634
I don't know
what came over me.

04:54.669 --> 04:56.834
It's just that
I feel violated.

04:56.869 --> 04:58.701
Someone's been in my home,
in my bedroom.

04:58.736 --> 05:00.167
I feel so helpless.

05:00.202 --> 05:04.334
We'd all feel helpless
in your bedroom, Marce.

05:04.369 --> 05:06.434
You got
any more beer?

05:06.469 --> 05:07.634
No.

05:07.669 --> 05:10.634
And in all the excitement,
I forgot to ask-

05:10.669 --> 05:13.534
Why are you meeting
in my house?

05:13.569 --> 05:16.667
Because our wives
didn't want you in ours.

05:16.702 --> 05:20.033
Hi. Did I
miss anything?

05:20.068 --> 05:23.067
You want me
back on my wife?

05:23.102 --> 05:24.434
Not on my account.

05:24.469 --> 05:26.501
I just wanted to say
I'm sorry you got robbed.

05:26.536 --> 05:28.100
It wasn't me.
It was them!

05:28.135 --> 05:29.501
Yeah, it was you.

05:29.536 --> 05:31.234
Somebody smashed
your car windshield,

05:31.269 --> 05:32.467
stole your radio,

05:32.502 --> 05:35.067
and wrote "wash me"
on your hood.

05:35.102 --> 05:37.267
My car!
They stole my radio?

05:37.302 --> 05:39.100
Hey, Bundy.
The thieves have a point.

05:39.135 --> 05:40.734
You really ought
to wash your car.

05:40.769 --> 05:42.501
Get out!

05:43.801 --> 05:44.968
Out! Out!

05:45.003 --> 05:48.000
Pretend there's a keg
on the lawn.

05:48.035 --> 05:48.968
Out! Out!

05:52.634 --> 05:55.501
I can't believe
they stole my radio

05:55.536 --> 05:57.367
right in front
of my house!

05:57.402 --> 05:58.834
I know how you feel.

05:58.869 --> 06:01.434
If you did, Steve,
you wouldn't be touching me.

06:01.469 --> 06:03.868
Maybe we should
get more involved

06:03.903 --> 06:05.467
with the
neighborhood watch.

06:05.502 --> 06:07.901
Look. You can't depend
on anybody but yourself.

06:07.936 --> 06:09.567
I've put this off long enough.

06:09.602 --> 06:11.267
I'm buying a gun.

06:11.302 --> 06:12.968
A gun is not the answer.

06:13.003 --> 06:15.467
You can't curtail
the criminal element

06:15.502 --> 06:17.367
by sinking
to their level.

06:17.402 --> 06:19.467
Oh, excuse me,
Miss Let's-run-them-over

06:19.502 --> 06:21.567
and-get-out
the-fishhooks.

06:21.602 --> 06:23.901
I was upset.
I wasn't thinking clearly.

06:23.936 --> 06:25.901
Yes. She wasn't
using the left,

06:25.936 --> 06:27.601
or analytical,
portion of the brain.

06:30.167 --> 06:33.067
I'm definitely
getting a gun.

06:33.102 --> 06:34.767
And I'd advise you
to do the same.

06:34.802 --> 06:37.868
Now, come on. There's got
to be a more humane way

06:37.903 --> 06:39.767
to protect our home
and possessions.

06:39.802 --> 06:40.901
There is.

06:40.936 --> 06:43.534
We'll get a dog.
A good watch dog.

06:43.569 --> 06:46.734
A dog. That's a great idea.
I've got a dog.

06:46.769 --> 06:49.400
Buck, look!
Strangers in the house!

06:49.435 --> 06:52.501
Kill them, Buck.
Go kill them!

06:52.536 --> 06:54.667
Whoa, big fella.

06:54.702 --> 06:57.400
I don't mean
a stupid dog.

06:57.435 --> 06:59.968
I'm talking
about a real dog.

07:00.003 --> 07:01.434
A guard dog.

07:01.469 --> 07:02.434
A Doberman.

07:02.469 --> 07:03.934
Steve,
first thing tomorrow,

07:03.969 --> 07:07.367
we're going to one of
those deadly doggy places.

07:07.402 --> 07:09.467
Yes, Al, because
we're against guns

07:09.502 --> 07:11.968
and the violence
they stand for.

07:12.003 --> 07:13.968
That's right. A dog.

07:14.003 --> 07:16.601
A vicious dog
with sharp teeth

07:16.636 --> 07:18.534
that will go
through a jugular

07:18.569 --> 07:21.467
like a hot knife cutting through
butter on a warm, summer night-

07:21.502 --> 07:22.801
Come along, dear.

07:22.836 --> 07:25.434
So that the next guy who tries
to get in my bedroom uninvited

07:25.469 --> 07:28.000
will walk out
on bloody stumps.

07:30.736 --> 07:32.601
When was the last time
you called

07:32.636 --> 07:34.734
to complain
about the dog?

07:34.769 --> 07:37.167
Yesterday. But Marcie
said to stop calling.

07:37.202 --> 07:39.000
She said the ringing
makes him bark.

07:39.035 --> 07:41.267
Everything
makes him bark.

07:41.302 --> 07:43.000
Hey, Dad, it's been
two weeks,

07:43.035 --> 07:45.234
and you haven't even
let me see the gun yet,

07:45.269 --> 07:47.100
let alone pick off
a pigeon or two.

07:47.135 --> 07:50.567
Bud, guns are not toys.
They are lethal weapons

07:50.602 --> 07:53.567
and should only be handled
by responsible adults.

07:53.602 --> 07:55.801
When Dad was practicing
his quick draws

07:55.836 --> 07:57.400
<i>at the TV
during Donahue-</i>

07:57.435 --> 07:59.467
Bud, number one,
shut up.

07:59.502 --> 08:01.801
Number two,
it was Phil's salute

08:01.836 --> 08:05.033
to the Huge and Fat
Women's Caucus.

08:05.068 --> 08:07.968
Number three, there
were no bullets in the gun.

08:08.003 --> 08:11.000
Your mother took them out
and hid them for safety reasons,

08:11.035 --> 08:12.567
and she won't tell me where.

08:12.602 --> 08:13.767
Guns, guns, guns.

08:13.802 --> 08:16.434
Can't anyone talk
about me for a change?

08:16.469 --> 08:19.534
Okay, Kelly.
Where were you last night?

08:19.569 --> 08:22.801
So, Dad, what kind
of gun did you buy?

08:25.536 --> 08:26.601
Coming!

08:33.000 --> 08:34.868
Hi, Peg.

08:34.903 --> 08:37.467
Borrow
a cup of kibble?

08:37.501 --> 08:40.433
We ran out, and
the dog's still hungry.

08:40.469 --> 08:41.667
What's the matter?

08:41.702 --> 08:44.467
The neighbor's cat
didn't fill him up?

08:44.502 --> 08:47.601
That cat was
taunting him, Al.

08:47.636 --> 08:50.133
Gee, you two
look cute.

08:50.168 --> 08:54.367
I can't get Al
to dress unisex at all.

08:54.402 --> 08:56.067
This is protective gear.

08:56.102 --> 08:57.968
You see, Bella still
hasn't accepted us

08:58.003 --> 08:59.501
as his rightful owners.

08:59.536 --> 09:02.167
You named that dog
after Bela Lugosi?

09:02.202 --> 09:04.400
No. Abzug.

09:04.435 --> 09:07.033
We thought
it was kind of cute.

09:07.068 --> 09:10.000
But he won't
wear the hat.

09:10.035 --> 09:11.601
Oh, listen Al,
by the way,

09:11.636 --> 09:14.400
we want to apologize
about your fence.

09:14.435 --> 09:15.767
What happened
to my fence?

09:15.802 --> 09:16.968
Bella ate
through it.

09:17.003 --> 09:18.501
Wow!

09:18.536 --> 09:19.834
It was just
a little piece.

09:19.869 --> 09:21.200
Yeah, not much, really.

09:21.235 --> 09:23.601
About the size
of a human face.

09:23.636 --> 09:26.601
Rhoades, what are we
going to do about this?

09:26.636 --> 09:29.133
Look, we'll handle this
the same way

09:29.168 --> 09:31.634
we dealt with
the cat incident.

09:31.669 --> 09:33.634
Get estimates,
and we'll make it good.

09:33.669 --> 09:36.100
Look, we know Bella
can be loud and annoying,

09:36.135 --> 09:39.000
and the whole neighborhood
hates his guts,

09:39.035 --> 09:40.834
but at least
he's a good protector.

09:40.869 --> 09:43.901
Gee, Mom, that's just
what you say about Dad.

09:45.767 --> 09:48.801
Mount up! They just
hit the Johnsons.

09:48.836 --> 09:50.501
TV and major appliances.

09:50.536 --> 09:53.501
We're meeting
at the Bowl and Brew

09:53.536 --> 09:55.100
to calm
ourselves down.

09:55.135 --> 09:56.501
Ha! See that!

09:56.536 --> 09:58.501
They didn't
hit our place.

09:58.536 --> 10:02.200
That's what a good dog
will do for you.

10:02.235 --> 10:05.033
Come on.
Grab the meal and the mace.

10:05.068 --> 10:07.367
It's time
to feed our doggy.

